# PRIVATE program markers for the public base's pre-push leak guard. The base reads
# ~/.dotlocal/git-leak-markers and uses its FIRST non-comment line as an extended-regex;
# any pushed commit whose content OR message matches is blocked. This keeps the private
# marker vocabulary in THIS (private) overlay, never in the public base.
#
# Uncomment + edit the line below with your private program's markers, e.g.:
#   (MYPROG|FOO)-[0-9]+|my-private-program-codename
#
# (No active line here = the marker scan is skipped; the generic key/overlay-URL guard still runs.)
